A simplicial complex with three vertices and three edges forms a triangle. In this case, the simplicial complex has the following faces:

1. Three 0-dimensional faces (the vertices): {A}, {B}, {C}
2. Three 1-dimensional faces (the edges): {A, B}, {B, C}, {C, A}
3. One 2-dimensional face (the triangle itself): {A, B, C}

So, the simplicial complex has a total of 7 faces.
